messageHandlers.script:
### Refresh data
	#system.perspective.print("Refresh Services Settings")
	#self.refreshBinding("props.data")
	#self.props.selection.selectedRow = None
	self.props.selection.selectedRow = -1

# implement your handler here
	import traceback
	try:
		#Send the dataset to Excel
		filename = 'Settings_services_' + str(system.date.format(system.date.now(),"yyyyMMddHHmmss")) + '.xls'
		dataset = self.props.data
		NewDataSet = []
		headers = ["Active","ServiceName","AllowUnder18","AssociatedPrograms","Comments"]
		for i in range(dataset.getRowCount()):
			NewDataSet.append([dataset.getValueAt(i,'active'),dataset.getValueAt(i,'serviceName'),dataset.getValueAt(i,'allowUnder18'),dataset.getValueAt(i,'programNames'),dataset.getValueAt(i,'serviceDescription')])	
			
		NewDataSet = system.dataset.toDataSet(headers, NewDataSet)

		xlFile = system.dataset.toExcel(True,NewDataSet)
		system.perspective.download(filename, xlFile)
	except:   
		logger = system.util.getLogger("Settings Services tableToExcel")
		msg = traceback.format_exc()
		logger.error(msg)

### Refresh data
	#system.perspective.print("Refresh Case Notes Data")
	view = self.view
	view.refreshBinding("custom.sql_data")
